l-ci/gradlew-2026-05-04T23-23-04-260348Z.log\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/checkstyle/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-04T23-25-12-362558Z.log\\n\",\"exit_code\":1,\"status\":\"failed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_29\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.aesh:readline:3.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5850-fails-javac-compile-org.aesh-readline-3.0-3d966204\\n\\nThe original failure was in `:compileTestJava`: `TerminalBuilderTest.java` and `SignalsTest.java` referenced non-existent packages/symbols (`package org.aesh.readline.terminal does not exist`, `package org.aesh.readline.terminal.utils does not exist`, plus follow-on `cannot find symbol` errors for `TerminalBuilder` and `Signals`). See `human-intervention-logs/org.aesh:readline:3.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T22-31-29-436862Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.aesh:readline:3.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-04T22-32-23-516744Z.log`.\\n\\nThe preserved branch appears to contain a working fix for that compile problem: later local CI reruns passed `checkMetadataFiles`, `run-consecutive-tests`, and `checkstyle` in `forge/logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-04T23-23-14-368111Z.log`, `forge/logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-04T23-23-22-637842Z.log`, `forge/logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-04T23-24-23-319643Z.log`, `forge/logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-04T23-24-24-782846Z.log`, and `forge/logs/checkstyle/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-04T23-25-12-362558Z.log`.\\n\\nThe most likely remaining failing stage is metadata generation / agent-based verification, not the final local CI suite. Multiple `generateMetadata` attempts failed with `Could not find agent library native-image-agent on the library path, with error: libnative-image-agent.so: cannot open shared object file`, followed by `Execution failed for task ':test'` / `:generateMetadata`. See `human-intervention-logs/org.aesh:readline:3.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-04T23-09-03-420911Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.aesh:readline:3.0/metadata-fix/codex.log`. Metrics were still written successfully in `stats/org.aesh/readline/3.0/execution-metrics.json`, which suggests the code/test changes progressed far enough to record coverage.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and rerun `generateMetadata` (or the nested `-Pagent test`) with a GraalVM JDK selected for the nested Gradle invocation so `native-image-agent` can be loaded.\\n2. If that passes, rerun the same local CI checks from the preserved branch and verify the generated metadata/tests before opening a PR.\\n3. If it still fails, inspect `human-intervention-logs/org.aesh:readline:3.0/metadata-fix/codex.log` together with the `native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-*.log` files to confirm which JDK the nested build is using.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":553272,\"cached_input_tokens\":476928,\"output_tokens\":9423,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":3543}}\n==== human-intervention-logs/org.aesh:readline:3.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-04T23-20-08-428683Z.log\n  +      },\n  +      \"glob\" : \"META-INF/services/org.assertj.core.configuration.Configuration\"\n  +    },\n  +    {\n  +      \"condition\" : {\n  +        \"typeReached\" : \"org_aesh.readline.JLineNativeLoaderTest\"\n  +      },\n  +      \"glob\" : \"META-INF/services/org.assertj.core.presentation.Representation\"\n  +    },\n  +    {\n  +      \"condition\" : {\n  +        \"typeReached\" : \"org.jline.terminal.spi.TerminalProvider\"\n  +      },\n  +      \"glob\" : \"META-INF/services/org/jline/terminal/provider/dumb\"\n  +    },\n  +    {\n  +      \"condition\" : {\n  +        \"typeReached\" : \"org.jline.nati